2x4.title: Niceness is the first line of defense
2x4.clickbait: The *first* line of defense in dealing with any partially superhuman AI system advanced enough to possibly be dangerous is that it does not *want* to hurt you or defeat your safety measures.
2x4.text:
The first line of defense in constructing any [2c sufficiently advanced] [42g Artificial General Intelligence] is building an AI that does not *want* to hurt you.  Any other measures, like [aibox AI-boxing] or trying to [airgap_ai prevent the AI from accessing the Internet], should be thought of only as backstops in case this first line of defense fails.  When designing the AGI we should first think as if all these [align_limit_oppose oppositional measures] don't exist, so that we aren't distracted while trying to envision an AGI that--[2x regardless] of [capability_gain how much power it has]--will not *want* to hurt us.

See also [nonadversarial the non-adversarial principle] and the distinction between [align_limit_oppose].
